    • Method Detail

      • setSkipAdDomainJoin

        public DeploymentTypeTypes.PscInfo.Builder setSkipAdDomainJoin(java.lang.Boolean skipAdDomainJoin)
        A flag to skip domain join operation for embedded node during convergence. If the Platform Services Controller node is joined to an AD domain, the same is expected to be configured for converged embedded node, but there can be situations (e.g. no domain admin credentials with VI admin) during convergence when needs to be done later via existing UI option. This property was added in vSphere API 6.7.2. If Set will skip AD domain join operations
        Parameters:
        skipAdDomainJoin - New value for the property.

      • setAdDomain

        public DeploymentTypeTypes.PscInfo.Builder setAdDomain(DeploymentTypeTypes.DomainInfo adDomain)
        Information about the domain which Platform Services Controller node is joined to. The reconfigured machine will be joined to the same domain. This property was added in vSphere API 6.7.2. If Set then converged embedded node will be joined to this AD domain.
        Parameters:
        adDomain - New value for the property.
